maxAgeMilliseconds

public CCDB2Parameters maxAgeMilliseconds(int i)
CCDB2 requires a maximum age of objects. Regardless of the TTL, objects will never live longer than this maximum. The default is 12 hours.

Parameters:
i - new maximum

backgroundPutLength

public CCDB2Parameters backgroundPutLength(int i)
Length for the background put queue. If greater than 0, put writes will occur in a background thread but the queue will block if it gets longer than the specified length. The default is 1000.

Parameters:
i - new value or 0
Returns:
this
